_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/743123316","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2065#issuecomment-743123316","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2065","id":743123316,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDc0MzEyMzMxNg==","user":{"login":"loximann","id":38527108,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4NTI3MTA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38527108?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann","html_url":"https://github.com/loximann","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-12-11T10:50:28Z","updated_at":"2020-12-11T10:50:28Z","body":"Hmmm, I beg to disagree, I think that the information contained in the header (Catch2 version, help hint, random seed) is something that should be shown or not independently of the test results and how they are reported. I for one want to have that info always, while not needing the successful test results (eg I may want to re-run with a successful seed on a different system).\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell, the --rng-seed must be explicitly given so that the seed is shown.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/743123316/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"loximann","id":38527108,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4NTI3MTA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38527108?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann","html_url":"https://github.com/loximann","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/loximann/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/743915266","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2065#issuecomment-743915266","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2065","id":743915266,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDc0MzkxNTI2Ng==","user":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-12-12T22:39:51Z","updated_at":"2020-12-12T22:39:51Z","body":"> As far as I can tell, the --rng-seed must be explicitly given so that the seed is shown.\r\n\r\nThis is not entirely true, but close enough for most cases. For reporters that support it, the actual rule is that the seed has to be different from 0 (because 0 is the default value).\r\n\r\nSee\r\n\r\n```\r\nxarn@DESKTOP-TJBO4PG:~/builds/Catch2/debug-v3-all$ ./tests/SelfTest -r xml --rng-seed 0 [matchers][approvals]~[failing] | head -n 5\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<Catch name=\"SelfTest\" filters=\"[matchers][approvals]~[failing]\">\r\n  <Group name=\"SelfTest\">\r\n    <TestCase name=\"Regex string matcher -- libstdc++-4.8 workaround\" tags=\"[approvals][matchers]\" filename=\"/mnt/c/ubuntu/Catch2/tests/SelfTest/UsageTests/Matchers.tests.cpp\" line=\"155\">\r\n      <OverallResult success=\"true\"/>\r\n```\r\nvs\r\n```\r\nxarn@DESKTOP-TJBO4PG:~/builds/Catch2/debug-v3-all$ ./tests/SelfTest -r xml --rng-seed 1 [matchers][approvals]~[failing] | head -n 5\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<Catch name=\"SelfTest\" filters=\"[matchers][approvals]~[failing]\">\r\n  <Randomness seed=\"1\"/>\r\n  <Group name=\"SelfTest\">\r\n    <TestCase name=\"Regex string matcher -- libstdc++-4.8 workaround\" tags=\"[approvals][matchers]\" filename=\"/mnt/c/ubuntu/Catch2/tests/SelfTest/UsageTests/Matchers.tests.cpp\" line=\"155\">\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nThe problem with the console reporter is that it doesn't report seed either way\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./tests/SelfTest --rng-seed 1 [matchers][approvals]~[failing]\r\nFilters: [matchers][approvals]~[failing]\r\n===============================================================================\r\nAll tests passed (19 assertions in 5 test cases)\r\n```\r\nThis means that if the user is using `--rng-seed time` together with the console (and after a quick test, also the compact reporter) the run is unrepeatable.\r\n\r\n\r\n-----------------------\r\n\r\nAs for what information should be displayed by default, I prefer the linuxish approach of not having too much output to stdout by default -- consider a tool like a compiler, would you want it to print out\r\n\r\n```\r\ng++ (Ubuntu 9.3.0-17ubuntu1~20.04) 9.3.0\r\nuse -h or --help for more options\r\nCopyright (C) 2019 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\r\n```\r\n\r\nafter each compiled file? ðŸ˜ƒ ","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/743915266/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/743917193","html_url":"h